parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Electrical system failures can cause fires, damage to components, and loss of vehicle functionality, potentially leading to accidents or injuries.
Ignition switch failures can cause fires, electrical shorts, and loss of vehicle functionality, potentially leading to accidents or injuries.
Alternator failures can cause electrical shorts, fires, and loss of vehicle functionality, potentially leading to accidents or injuries.
Distributor mounted TFI module failures can cause vehicle stalling, potentially leading to accidents or injuries.

Unwanted acceleration can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, and injuries. It can also lead to rear-ending other vehicles, crashing into objects, or experiencing sudden and unexpected movements.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates suddenly and unexpectedly
often without pressing the accelerator pedal
the vehicle moves forward while the brake pedal is pressed
the vehicle accelerates out of control
the cruise control fails to disengage
the idle speed control module fails.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Transmission Failure due to Plastic Bushing Deterioration
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the plastic bushing in the transmission can cause the transmission to become damaged, leading to difficulties in shifting gears, and potentially causing accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
The failure of the axle can cause the wheel to come off, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
The failure of the seat belt can increase the risk of injury or fatality in the event of an accident.
